summary: The document is an FBI agent's report detailing the investigation of David Reed FROMER, a person of interest from 1960 to 1966, in relation to the JFK assassination. It outlines the submission of specific forms (DD Form 398 and DD Form 98) to the FBI's San Francisco Office and notes the coordination between the FBI and the Department of the Army. The document was reviewed and approved for release with certain deletions in 1997.
key_findings: David Reed FROMER was investigated by the FBI from May 3, 1960, to November 23, 1966.
Forms DD Form 398 and DD Form 98 were submitted to the San Francisco Office of the FBI.
There was coordination between the FBI and the Department of the Army, with all pertinent reports provided to the latter.
The document was deemed releasable with deletions on October 15, 1997.
